#. Tag: title
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "Apache Configuration"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you install <systemitem class=\"resource\">apache2-mod-apparmor</"
"systemitem>, make sure the module is enabled, and then restart Apache by "
"executing the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "a2enmod apparmor &amp;&amp; sudo systemctl reload apache2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Apache is configured by placing directives in plain text configuration "
"files. The main configuration file is usually <filename>/etc/apache2/httpd."
"conf</filename>. When you compile Apache, you can indicate the location of "
"this file. Directives can be placed in any of these configuration files to "
"alter the way Apache behaves. When you make changes to the main "
"configuration files, you need to reload Apache with <command>sudo systemctl "
"reload apache2</command>, so the changes are recognized."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "Virtual Host Directives"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;VirtualHost&gt; and &lt;/VirtualHost&gt; directives are used to enclose "
"a group of directives that will apply only to a particular virtual host. For "
"more information on Apache virtual host directives, refer to <link xlink:"
"href=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/en/mod/core.html#virtualhost\"></"
"link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The ChangeHat-specific configuration keyword is <literal>AADefaultHatName</"
"literal>. It is used similarly to <literal>AAHatName</literal>, for example, "
"<literal>AADefaultHatName My_Funky_Default_Hat</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It allows you to specify a default hat to be used for virtual hosts and "
"other Apache server directives, so that you can have different defaults for "
"different virtual hosts. This can be overridden by the <literal>AAHatName</"
"literal> directive and is checked for only if there is not a matching "
"<literal>AAHatName</literal> or hat named by the URI. If the "
"<literal>AADefaultHatName</literal> hat does not exist, it falls back to the "
"<literal>DEFAULT_URI</literal> hat if it exists/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If none of those are matched, it goes back to the <quote>parent</quote> "
"Apache hat."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "Location and Directory Directives"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Location and directory directives specify hat names in the program "
"configuration file so the Apache calls the hat regarding its security. For "
"Apache, you can find documentation about the location and directory "
"directives at <link xlink:href=\"http://httpd.apache.org/docs/2.4/en/"
"sections.html\"></link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The location directive example below specifies that, for a given location, "
"<literal>mod_apparmor</literal> should use a specific hat:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;Location /foo/&gt;\n"
"  AAHatName MY_HAT_NAME\n"
"&lt;/Location&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:193
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This tries to use <literal>MY_HAT_NAME</literal> for any URI beginning with "
"<filename>/foo/</filename> (<filename>/foo/</filename>, <filename>/foo/bar</"
"filename>, <filename>/foo/cgi/path/blah_blah/blah</filename>, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The directory directive works similarly to the location directive, except it "
"refers to a path in the file system as in the following example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;Directory \"/srv/www/www.example.org/docs\"&gt; \n"
"  # Note lack of trailing slash \n"
"  AAHatName example.org \n"
"&lt;/Directory&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing ChangeHat-Aware Applications"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the previous section you learned about <literal>mod_apparmor</literal> "
"and the way it helps you to secure a specific Web application. This section "
"walks you through a real-life example of creating a hat for a Web "
"application, and using &aa;'s change_hat feature to secure it. Note that "
"this chapter focuses on &aa;'s command line tools, as &yast;'s &aa; module "
"has limited functionality."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "With &aa;'s Command Line Tools"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For illustration purposes, let us choose the Web application called "
"<emphasis>Adminer</emphasis> (<link xlink:href=\"http://www.adminer.org/en/"
"\"></link>). It is a full-featured SQL database management tool written in "
"PHP, yet consisting of a single PHP file. For Adminer to work, you need to "
"set up an Apache Web server, PHP and its Apache module, and one of the "
"database drivers available for PHP&mdash;&mysql; in this example. You can "
"install the required packages with"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:232
#, no-c-format
msgid "zypper in apache2 apache2-mod_apparmor apache2-mod_php5 php5 php5-mysql"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:234
#, no-c-format
msgid "To set up the Web environment for running Adminer, follow these steps:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:239
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting Up a Web Server Environment"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure <literal>apparmor</literal> and <literal>php5</literal> modules "
"are enabled for Apache. To enable the modules in any case, use:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:245
#, no-c-format
msgid "a2enmod apparmor php5"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:246
#, no-c-format
msgid "and then restart Apache with"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:249 apparmor_changehat.xml:336
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo systemctl restart apache2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:252
#, no-c-format
msgid "Make sure &mysql; is running. If unsure, restart it with"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:255
#, no-c-format
msgid "sudo systemctl restart mysql"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"taroth 2014-02-26: at the moment, there is no mariadb.service, starting "
"mysql seems to be the right way - wrote mail to mhrusecky to ask if this is "
"bound to change anytime soon for SLE 12"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Download Adminer from <link xlink:href=\"http://www.adminer.org\"></link>, "
"copy it to <filename>/srv/www/htdocs/adminer/</filename>, and rename it to "
"<filename>adminer.php</filename>, so that its full path is <filename>/srv/"
"www/htdocs/adminer/adminer.php</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:270
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Test Adminer in your Web browser by entering <literal>http://localhost/"
"adminer/adminer.php</literal> in its URI address field. If you installed "
"Adminer to a remote server, replace <literal>localhost</literal> with the "
"real host name of the server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:277
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adminer Login Page"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you encounter problems viewing the Adminer login page, try to look for "
"help in the Apache error log <filename>/var/log/apache2/error.log</"
"filename>. Another reason you cannot access the Web page may be that your "
"Apache is already under &aa; control and its &aa; profile is too tight to "
"permit viewing Adminer. Check it with <command>aa-status</command>, and if "
"needed, set Apache temporarily in complain mode with"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:296
#, no-c-format
msgid "aa-complain usr.sbin.httpd2-prefork"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the Web environment for Adminer is ready, you need to configure "
"Apache's mod_apparmor, so that &aa; can detect accesses to Adminer and "
"change to the specific <quote>hat</quote>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:308
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring mod_apparmor"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:310
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Apache has several configuration files under <filename>/etc/apache2/</"
"filename> and <filename>/etc/apache2/conf.d/</filename>. Choose your "
"preferred one and open it in a text editor. In this example, the "
"<command>vim</command> editor is used to create a new configuration file "
"<filename>/etc/apache2/conf.d/apparmor.conf</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:318
#, no-c-format
msgid "vim /etc/apache2/conf.d/apparmor.conf"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:321
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copy the following snippet into the edited file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;Directory /srv/www/htdocs/adminer&gt;\n"
"  AAHatName adminer\n"
"&lt;/Directory&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:325
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It tells Apache to let &aa; know about a change_hat event when the Web user "
"accesses the directory <filename>/adminer</filename> (and any file/directory "
"inside) in Apache's document root. Remember, we placed the <filename>adminer."
"php</filename> application there."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:333
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save the file, close the editor, and restart Apache with"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Apache now knows about our Adminer and changing a <quote>hat</quote> for it. "
"It is time to create the related hat for Adminer in the &aa; configuration. "
"If you do not have an &aa; profile yet, create one before proceeding. "
"Remember that if your Apache's main binary is <filename>/usr/sbin/httpd2-"
"prefork</filename>, then the related profile is named <filename>/etc/"
"apparmor.d/usr.sbin.httpd2-prefork</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:350
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Hat for Adminer"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open (or create one if it does not exist) the file <filename>/etc/apparmor.d/"
"usr.sbin.httpd2-prefork</filename> in a text editor. Its contents should be "
"similar to the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:357
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"#include &lt;tunables/global&gt;\n"
"\n"
"/usr/sbin/httpd2-prefork {\n"
"  #include &lt;abstractions/apache2-common&gt;\n"
"  #include &lt;abstractions/base&gt;\n"
"  #include &lt;abstractions/php5&gt;\n"
"\n"
"  capability kill,\n"
"  capability setgid,\n"
"  capability setuid,\n"
"\n"
"  /etc/apache2/** r,\n"
"  /run/httpd.pid rw,\n"
"  /usr/lib{,32,64}/apache2*/** mr,\n"
"  /var/log/apache2/** rw,\n"
"\n"
"  ^DEFAULT_URI {\n"
"    #include &lt;abstractions/apache2-common&gt;\n"
"    /var/log/apache2/** rw,\n"
"  }\n"
"\n"
"  ^HANDLING_UNTRUSTED_INPUT {\n"
"    #include &lt;abstractions/apache2-common&gt;\n"
"    /var/log/apache2/** w,\n"
"  }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before the last closing curly bracket (<literal>}</literal>), insert the "
"following section:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"^adminer flags=(complain) {\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note the <literal>(complain)</literal> addition after the hat name&mdash;it "
"tells &aa; to leave the <systemitem>adminer</systemitem> hat in complain "
"mode. That is because we need to learn the hat profile by accessing Adminer "
"later on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "@cboltz: i did it this way myself and it worked perfectly"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:374
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save the file, and then restart &aa;, then Apache."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:377
#, no-c-format
msgid "systemctl reload apparmor apache2"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:380
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Check if the <systemitem>adminer</systemitem> hat really is in complain mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# aa-status \n"
"apparmor module is loaded.\n"
"39 profiles are loaded.\n"
"37 profiles are in enforce mode.\n"
"[...]\n"
"   /usr/sbin/httpd2-prefork\n"
"   /usr/sbin/httpd2-prefork//DEFAULT_URI\n"
"   /usr/sbin/httpd2-prefork//HANDLING_UNTRUSTED_INPUT\n"
"[...]\n"
"2 profiles are in complain mode.\n"
"   /usr/bin/getopt\n"
"   /usr/sbin/httpd2-prefork//adminer\n"
"[...]"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:385
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As we can see, the <literal>httpd2-prefork//adminer</literal> is loaded in "
"complain mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:392
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Our last task is to find out the right set of rules for the "
"<systemitem>adminer</systemitem> hat. That is why we set the "
"<systemitem>adminer</systemitem> hat into complain mode&mdash;the logging "
"facility collects useful information about the access requirements of "
"<filename>adminer.php</filename> as we use it via the Web browser. "
"<command>aa-logprof</command> then helps us with creating the hat's profile."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:403
#, no-c-format
msgid "Generating Rules for the <systemitem>adminer</systemitem> Hat"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:405
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open Adminer in the Web browser. If you installed it locally, then the URI "
"is <literal>http://localhost/adminer/adminer.php</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:411
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose the database engine you want to use (&mysql; in our case), and log in "
"to Adminer using the existing database user name and password. You do not "
"need to specify the database name as you can do so after logging in. Perform "
"any operations with Adminer you like&mdash;create a new database, create a "
"new table for it, set user privileges, and so on."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:421
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the short testing of Adminer's user interface, switch back to console "
"and examine the log for collected data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:425
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"# aa-logprof \n"
"Reading log entries from /var/log/messages.\n"
"Updating AppArmor profiles in /etc/apparmor.d.\n"
"Complain-mode changes:\n"
"\n"
"Profile:  /usr/sbin/httpd2-prefork^adminer\n"
"Path:     /dev/urandom\n"
"Mode:     r\n"
"Severity: 3\n"
"\n"
"  1 - #include &lt;abstractions/apache2-common&gt;\n"
"[...]  \n"
" [8 - /dev/urandom]\n"
"\n"
"[(A)llow] / (D)eny / (G)lob / Glob w/(E)xt / (N)ew / Abo(r)t / (F)inish / "
"(O)pts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:426
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the <command>aa-logprof</command> message, it is clear that our new "
"<systemitem>adminer</systemitem> hat was correctly detected:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:430
#, no-c-format
msgid "Profile:  /usr/sbin/httpd2-prefork^adminer"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:431
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>aa-logprof</command> command will ask you to pick the right "
"rule for each discovered &aa; event. Specify the one you want to use, and "
"confirm with <guimenu>Allow</guimenu>. For more information on working with "
"the <command>aa-genprof</command> and <command>aa-logprof</command> "
"interface, see <xref linkend=\"sec.apparmor.commandline.profiling.summary."
"genprof\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apparmor_changehat.xml:440
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<command>aa-logprof</command> usually offers several valid rules for the "
"examined event. Some are <emphasis>abstractions</emphasis>&mdash;predefined "
"sets of rules affecting a specific common group of targets. Sometimes it is "
"useful to include such an abstraction instead of a direct URI rule:"
